<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="528" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,799,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="528">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic, 1921" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1921" box="[761,1115,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiontochananus">
<emphasis box="[761,973,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="528">L. kiontochananus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pic" box="[994,1107,799,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="528" refString="Pic, M. (1921) Nouveautes diverses. Melanges Exotico-Entomologiques, 33, 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1921">
Pic, 
<number box="[1050,1107,800,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="528" value="1921.0">1921</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer" box="[1168,1350,799,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="528" refString="Wittmer, W. (1982) 71. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Cantharidae. Entomologica Basiliensia, 7, 340 - 347." type="journal article" year="1982">
Wittmer (
<number box="[1281,1342,800,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="528" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In the present study, it is reinstated as a valid species, since that its abdominal sternite VIII and antennae of the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,836,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="528">holotype</typeStatus>
